    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the \"both sides\" thing but that feels a bit like an easy way out. like, if we look at the actual outcomes in countries that have it vs the US, isn't it pretty clear that the \"human right\" argument is more grounded in reality? it's hard to call it just an \"opinion\" when people are literally dying without care.",
