      "content": "The stark reality of preventable deaths in the US compared to nations with universal coverage is undeniable proof that healthcare access is a moral imperative, not a mere policy preference. When human lives are at stake, the argument for a fundamental right becomes an ethical necessity, not just a political talking point. Therefore, the evidence overwhelmingly supports the view that universal healthcare is a basic human right that societies must guarantee.",
      "source": "target",
